            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 17,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1466341212,
            "creation_date": 1466336804,
            "body": "<p>Use a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decompiler\" rel=\"noreferrer\">decompiler<\/a>. I prefer using <a href=\"https://github.com/fesh0r/fernflower\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Fernflower<\/a>, or if you use IntelliJ IDEA, simply open .class files from there, because it has Fernflower pre-installed.<\/p>\n\n<p>Or, go to <a href=\"http://javadecompilers.com\" rel=\"noreferrer\">javadecompilers.com<\/a>, upload your .jar file, use CFR and download the decompiled .zip file.<\/p>\n\n<p>However, in some cases, decompiling code is quite illegal, so, prefer to learn instead of decompiling.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 37906893,
            "question_id": 37906786,
            "last_edit_date": 1466341212
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/zOIoOym5.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 10749738,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 7909654,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7909654/aahash",
                "reputation": 71,
                "display_name": "Aahash"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 5,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1494691864,
            "creation_date": 1494691511,
            "body": "<h3>Extract the Contents of <code>.zip<\/code>/<code>.jar<\/code> files programmatically<\/h3>\n\n<p>Suppose <code>.jar<\/code> file is the <code>.jar<\/code>/<code>.zip<\/code> file to be extracted. <code>destDir<\/code> is the path where it will be extracted:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>java.util.jar.JarFile jar = new java.util.jar.JarFile(jarFile);\njava.util.Enumeration enum = jar.entries();\nwhile (enum.hasMoreElements()) {\n    java.util.jar.JarEntry file = (java.util.jar.JarEntry) enum.nextElement();\n    java.io.File f = new java.io.File(destDir + java.io.File.separator + file.getName());\n    if (file.isDirectory()) { // if its a directory, create it\n        f.mkdir();\n        continue;\n    }\n    java.io.InputStream is = jar.getInputStream(file); // get the input stream\n    java.io.FileOutputStream fos = new java.io.FileOutputStream(f);\n    while (is.available() &gt; 0) {  // write contents of 'is' to 'fos'\n        fos.write(is.read());\n    }\n    fos.close();\n    is.close();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 43955213,
            "question_id": 37906786,
            "last_edit_date": 1494691864
        }
    ],
